(You can get a virus from e-mail by opening attachments. Here's a 
hint of advice: Don't open file attachments! You can open them if the 
person told you they were sending you something before-hand. exe. are 
especially the ones that hold viruses. You should have your anti-
virus system updated. You could go to the norton anti-virus website 
or the microsoft website, or what ever anti-virus system you use.)


Rattrap:



Rattrap holed himself in a homemade den. Several days passed without 
incident with other bots, thank Primus. No sightings meant that they 
weren't going to report that Rattrap was around, so they wouldn't 
take that to Hell Beast. 

Running was his only option. It wasn't his best idea, but it got him 
away from the torcher chamber. He sniffed around the exit-way of his 
little den, shaking his whiskers, testing the air, making sure no one 
was around, then he pulled his body out of it. He looked around. All 
clear, just like everyday.

He went deeper inside of the forest where he found more edible 
berries. Those things were the only thing keeping his stomach from 
aching from hunger. He stood up and leaned on the branched, pulling 
the red berries off with his front teeth.
